cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.CV

The paper discusses a security attack on deep learning systems, specifically on neural architecture search (NAS) used in Machine Learning as a Service (MLaaS). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves deep learning architectures and pipelines, which suggests it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of the algorithm in PyTorch and Tensorflow, which could indicate it belongs to cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
